Activity Summary: Type of compound activity based on both the FXR agonist mode screen and the cell viability and auto fluorescence counter screens.
Ratio Activity: Type of compound activity in the ratio readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
Ratio Potency (uM): The concentration of sample yielding half-maximal activation in the ratio readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
Ratio Efficacy (%): Percent activation in the ratio readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
530 nm Activity: Type of compound activity in the 530 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
530 nm Potency (uM): The concentration of sample yielding half-maximal activation in the 530 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
530 nm Efficacy (%): Percent activation in the 530 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
460 nm Activity: Type of compound activity in the 460 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
460 nm Potency (uM): The concentration of sample yielding half-maximal activation in the 460 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
460 nm Efficacy (%): Percent activation in the 460 nm readout of the FXR agonist mode screen.
Viability Activity: Type of activity in the cell viability counter screen.
Viability Potency (uM): The concentration of sample yielding half-maximal inhibition in the cell viability screen.
Viability Efficacy (%): Percent inhibition in the cell viability counter screen.
Blue (460 nm) auto fluorescence outcome: Type of compound activity in the auto fluorescence counter screens.
